      <description>&lt;figure class=&#34;right xsmall&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;a target=&#34;_blank&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12543.Bird_by_Bird&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;img src=&#34;https://images.gr-assets.com/books/1394996112l/12543.jpg&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;We don&amp;rsquo;t have much truth to express unless we have gone into those rooms and closets and woods and abysses that we were told not go in to. When we have gone in and looked around for a long while, just breathing and finally taking it in &amp;ndash; then we will be able to speak in our own voice and to stay in the present moment. And that moment is home.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;span class=&#34;right&#34;&gt;&amp;ndash; Bird by Bird&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
